parameters:
\N<Tseda>Ku, kuku... Feeling relieved? He's just asleep for now...
but, you might want to worry...?

\N<Tseda>To withstand the poison of these ruins... the power of Mind
Luda is essential. That goes for me, you... Rozaro, and
that child as well...

\N<Tseda>As I said... I've taken measures. That child is an important
hostage, after all... But... it's about time... for them to
show up.

\N<Segi>What are you talking about...!? Answer me clearly! What did
you do to this child!?

\N<Tseda>Why do you think we can be here...? I mentioned the effects
of Mind Luda, didn't I...? I used the same thing on him...

\N<Tseda>A secret potion that grants power... In other words, it's a
potent drug that can even enhance one's body to that
extent... What do you think will happen if you administer it
to such a child...?
\N<Segi>Riia!! Are you okay!? Mama is right here!

\N<Segi>(I remember Zuuteruka saying long ago. He came to
investigate the ruins of this town...)

\N<Segi>(And now... this place is indeed the innermost part of the
ruins...)

\N<Segi>(Beyond here, something that Zuuteruka and Luda sought must
be lying in wait...?)

\N<Segi>(The thing Luda sought... that must be something they
absolutely need to have in their possession)

\N<Segi>(Maybe something necessary to defeat Luda is sleeping
beyond here...)

\N<Segi>(But no, I can't... Time is of the essence right now... I
must get Riia to a doctor quickly...)

\N<Riia>Haah... ha... ah... Mama... it's okay, right...? I can
handle it... so...

\N<Segi>...Understood. Riia, can you bear it just a little longer?
Just for a little while.

\N<Riia>Yeah... I'm fine, I can handle it. Because Mama has...
things she still needs to do here, right...?

\N<Riia>...I'll be fine. After all, Mama has... w-well, there are
still things you need to do here, right...?

\N<Segi>It won't open...? There's just some strange pattern in the
center...

\N<Segi>This looks like... a hole for something with a special shape
to fit into...

\N<Segi>There's no other keyhole or knob on the door. If that's the
case, then surely this must be the key to opening it.

\N<Segi>There's moss growing thickly in the slight gap between the
door and the other side. That means this door has been
closed for a very long time.

\N<Segi>Which means... Zuuteruka, who was supposed to have
investigated this place years ago, was also stopped here...?

\N<Segi>But the shape of this indentation on the door... I've seen
it somewhere...

\N<Segi>No, it's nothing. Come on, let's go to the doctor's quickly?
You'll feel better in no time.
\N<Riia>Hey, Mom... this uneven pattern... could it be...

\N<Riia>It looks like the pattern on the necklace that Dad used to
wear.

\N<Segi>If I place Lord Yuia's necklace into this indentation on the
door...

\N<Segi>It opened... So it really was Lord Yuia's necklace that was
the key.

\N<Segi>Lord Yuia and the Princess Consort... What could their
family have been protecting so fervently beyond here...?
